The paper involves the use of convolutional neural networks (CNN) for viewpoint prediction, which is a common technique in computer vision (cs.CV). It also deals with network resource allocation and optimization, which falls under the category of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The paper also involves the use of probability distributions and optimization algorithms, which are common in machine learning (cs.MM) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper deals with streaming video, which is a common topic in distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
